Middle East'' (Hurst, 2014).\n* Walker, Dennis.  \"Mustafa Kamil\u2019s Party: Islam, Pan-Islamism, and Nationalism\", ''Islam in the Modern Age,'' Vol. 11 (1980), 230\u20139 and Vol. 12 (1981), 1\u201343\n\n===Primary sources===\n* Cromer, Earl of. ''Modern Egypt'' (2 vol 1908) [https://archive.org/details/modernegypt00crom online free]  1220pp\n* Milner, Alfred. ''England in Egypt'' (London, 1892). [https://archive.org/details/englandinegypt03milngoog online]\n* Amira Sonbol, ed. ''The Last Khedive of Egypt: Memoirs of Abbas Hilmi II'' (Reading, UK: Ithaca Press, 1998).\n\n{{Subdivisions of the Ottoman Empire|expanded = Vassals}}\n{{Egypt topics}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{coord|30|03|N|31|13|E|type:country_source:kolossus-ptwiki|display=title}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Khedivate of Egypt}}\n[[Category:States and territories established in 1867]]\n[[Category:States and territories disestablished in 1914]]\n[[Category:19th century in Egypt]]\n[[Category:20th century in Egypt]]\n[[Category:British colonisation in Africa]]\n[[Category:Egypt under the Muhammad Ali dynasty]]\n[[Category:Former countries in the Middle East|Egypt Khedivate]]\n[[Category:History of Egypt (1900\u2013present)]]\n[[Category:New Imperialism]]\n[[Category:Ottoman Egypt]]\n[[Category:Vassal and tributary states of the Ottoman Empire]]\n[[Category:1867 establishments in Africa]]\n[[Category:1914 disestablishments in Africa]]\n[[Category:1860s establishments in the Ottoman Empire]]\n[[Category:20th-century disestablishments in Egypt]]\n", "name_user": "Havsj\u00f6", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khedivate_of_Egypt"}
